<font color="#FF0000">INFLUENCE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun  3 12:35:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
After much thought on this issue, I believe that I have to side with Andy on this issue, but from a slightly different slant. I am willing to try anything that may have an impact on: closing the re-education camps, helping those that assisted us while incountry, helping the kids of those same who suffered the consequences of AO, providing hospitals for these same people, etc.. I fail to see how these motives would dishonor those names on the Wall. The would be merely extention of what many believe our purposes were back then.<br><br>
Saying that, we must not allow our leaders to NOT link money and businesses invested in their economy with these changes. We must not allow prisons and camps to be slave factories as is the case in other countries. Nor to exploit the populace in the name of corporate greed!
